an, the evening of Bonfire.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"3\" title=\"Day 3: Rishikesh\"]Celebrate the most awaited festival Holi, play with colours, eat mouth watering sweets and dance on the tunes of the classic Bollywood Holi music. In the evening, attend one of its kind - Parmarth Ashram’s Prayer at the banks of river Ganges.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Rishikesh\"]This is the day to yourself and to relax. Attend Yoga class, go for ayurvedic massage, or spend some time chilling in the famous Beatles cafe.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Rishikesh-Delhi\"]Hop on the train to Delhi, in the evening we will either watch a Bollywood movie or catch a live traditional dance show or theatre, depending on the availability.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"6\" title=\"Day 6: Delhi - Agra - Delhi\"]We depart towards Agra in the morning and as the afternoon approaches its time to soak into the wonders of Taj Mahal, the elegant symbol of love. We return to Delhi on the same day.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"7\" title=\"Day 7: Delhi\"]After breakfast, begin this day by exploring Old and New Delhi, with visits to historical and religious sights as well as stroll through the most fashionable Delhi market for shopping.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"8\" title=\"Day 8: Delhi-Namchi via Bagdogra\"]Take a flight to Bagdogra airport and then a taxi to reach Namchi. This is a long day as today we enter the most beautiful state of India - ‘Sikkim’ and continue our onward journey. You get to spend the evening to yourself.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"9\" title=\"Day 9: Namchi-Pelling\"]Visit Tendong Hill and Char Dham in Namchi and in the Afternoon, take the mesmerising route to Pelling, appreciating the beauty of this natural wonder.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"10\" title=\"Day 10: Pelling\"]This day we visit the beautiful Kanchenjunga Falls, Khecheopalri Lake and Pemayangtse Monastery. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"11\" title=\"Day 11: Pelling\"]This is a special day as today we will spend some memorable time in an NGO with some adorable kids. And later walk upto Rabdanse Ruins to enjoy the spectacular views of the Kanchendzong hill ranges.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"12\" title=\"Day 12: Pelling-Darjeeling\"]After breakfast, we will leave for Darjeeling- ‘The Queen of Hills’. On the way we will see Tea farms and visit a Japanese temple. We spend the evening relaxing and everyone is encouraged to explore the locality.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"13\" title=\"Day 13: Darjeeling\"]Visit Tiger Hill situated at an altitude of 8000 feet for an amazing view of Mount Kanchenjunga and then sight seeing of Darjeeling. In the evening we’ll enjoy a farewell group dinner and one last night out together before we part ways at the end of this most memorable trip.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"14\" title=\"Day 14: Darjeeling-Bagdogra Airport-Delhi Airport\"]Time to bid adieu. Check out from hotel and transfer to Bagdogra airport via taxi for your return flight from Delhi Airport. (Total travel time to reach Delhi Airport from Darjeeling is 5.5 hours).\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item]<strong>End of this memorable tour.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/timeline]\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:8:\"Location\";s:7:\"content\";s:153:\"<pre><code></code>[google_map_embed src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=1PDRbfivSbvgf6cV9Xi3Dz8gOMYU\" height=\"400\" width_mode=\"box-width\"]</pre>\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Terms and Conditions\";s:7:\"content\";s:1253:\"<strong>Terms and conditions:</strong> Expedition cost: 1545 USD\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>To confirm your spot, you can pay 100 USD (this is a non-refundable amount)</li>\r\n 	<li>You will have to pay a deposit of 650 USD before 1st January 2017 for us to proceed with the bookings.</li>\r\n 	<li>Rest of the amount : has to be paid before 1st Feb 2017.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Cancellation policy:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>100 USD is non-refundable.</li>\r\n 	<li>95% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 75 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>75% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 60 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>50% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 45 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>25% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 30 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>15% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 15 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>No refund afterwards.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nFor more information you can also drop us an email at: info@yourholidayagent.com, or call us at: +91 9731587004 or whatsapp: +91 9731587004, viber: +919731587004\";}}}'),(2239,1382,'_tax_status','taxable'),(2240,1382,'_tax_class',''),(2241,1382,'slide_template','default'),(2242,1382,'tour_booking_periods','a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:11:\"exact_dates\";a:1:{i:0;s:10:\"2017-03-11\";}s:5:\"limit\";s:2:\"12\";s:10:\"spec_price\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"mode\";s:11:\"exact-dates\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";s:4:\"from\";s:10:\"2017-03-11\";s:2:\"to\";s:10:\"2017-03-11\";}}'),(2243,1382,'_product_version','2.6.14'),(2244,1382,'_variable_tour','no'),(2245,1382,'_vc_post_settings','a:1:{s:10:\"vc_grid_id\";a:0:{}}'),(2246,1382,'_edit_lock','1491942193:1'),(2247,1382,'_edit_last','1'),(2248,1382,'_product_image_gallery','1384,1385,1386,1387,1388,1389,1390,1391,1392,1393,1394,1395,1396,1397,1398,1399,1400,1401,1402,1403,1404'),(2249,1382,'_thumbnail_id','1405'),(2250,1382,'total_sales','0'),(2251,1382,'_sku',''),(2258,1384,'_w