 3: Nathu La Pass and Changu Lake\"]Visit the beautiful and holy Tsomgo or Changu Lake which is just 5 Km from China border. Next stop is the mighty mountain pass of Nathu La and Baba Mandir. Nathu La pass is considered as one of the highest motorable mountain passes in the world.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Gangtok-Pelling\"]After breakfast, take the mesmerising route to Pelling, appreciating the beauty of this natural wonder. On the way, visit the archaeological site- Rabdentse Ruins and Pemayangtse Monastery. In the evening, trek for around 3 km\'s to see one of the most beautiful Monasteries and astounding views of Pelling while trekking up. Overnight stay at Pelling.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Pelling\"]This day we visit the majestic Kanchenjunga Falls, Khecheopalri Lake and Sing Shoe Bridge. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills. If weather permits, we will trek up to a hidden, untouched and pure waterfall which we discovered on our past trip and named it ‘Pawan Falls’ after the guy who helped us in finding it.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"6\" title=\"Day 6: Pelling-Namchi\"]After breakfast, we say goodbye to Pelling to reach Namchi. On the way visit Char Dham and Buddha park in Rawangla. We finish this memorable trip in a musical way. Time for some Karaoke!!! We sing our heart out and dance with our local host- ‘Minu’.[/timeline_item]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[timeline_item item_number=\"7\" title=\"Day 7: Namchi-Bagdogra Airport\"]Time to bid adieu. Check out from the hotel and transfer to Bagdogra airport via taxi for your onward journey.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[/timeline_item]</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><strong><span class=\"s1\">End of this memorable tour.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">[/timeline]</span></p>\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Terms and Conditions\";s:7:\"content\";s:1376:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Terms and conditions:</strong> Total trip cost: 23999 INR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe government of Sikkim issue only limited permits for Nathula pass which is based on the lottery. We will not be liable for any claims or expenses to not cover Nathula pass if don’t get the permit.\r\n\r\nPlease note: we will not be liable for any claims or expenses arising from circumstances beyond our control such as accidents, injuries, delayed or cancelled flights/trains &amp; acts or forces of nature. The client will have to bear the charges of cancellation (if charged by the hotel &amp; other suppliers) arising due to delayed or cancelled flights/trains &amp; acts or forces of nature.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"list-style-type: none;\"><strong>Cancellation policy:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>75% of your booking amount will be refunded if you cancel your participation before 45 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>50% of your booking amount will be refunded if you cancel your participation before 30 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>25% of your booking amount will be refunded if you cancel your participation before 15 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>No refund afterwards.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nFor more information you can also drop us an email at: info@yourholidayagent.com, Call us at: +91 9731587004,  +919818141240, WhatsApp: +91 9731587004 or Viber: +919731587004</li>\r\n</ul>\";}}}'),(4530,1882,'_tax_status','taxable'),(4531,1882,'_tax_class',''),(4532,1882,'slide_template','default'),(4533,1882,'tour_booking_periods','a:2:{i:0;a:7:{s:4:\"from\";s:10:\"2017-04-29\";s:2:\"to\";s:10:\"2017-05-05\";s:4:\"days\";a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"Sat\";}s:5:\"limit\";s:2:\"12\";s:10:\"spec_price\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"mode\";s:7:\"default\";s:4:\"type\";s:1:\"1\";}i:1;a:7:{s:4:\"from\";s:10:\"20