(4617,1896,'_crosssell_ids','a:0:{}'),(4618,1896,'header_section_meta','a:8:{s:12:\"section_mode\";s:6:\"banner\";s:17:\"header_section_id\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"slider_alias\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"banner_subtitle\";s:15:\"6 Nights/7 Days\";s:12:\"banner_image\";s:67:\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/nubra-valley-leh.jpg\";s:24:\"is_banner_image_parallax\";s:1:\"1\";s:19:\"banner_image_repeat\";s:9:\"no-repeat\";s:11:\"banner_mask\";s:0:\"\";}'),(4619,1896,'tour_tabs_meta','a:2:{s:10:\"tour_badge\";s:1:\"2\";s:4:\"tabs\";a:2:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:9:\"Itinerary\";s:7:\"content\";s:2578:\"[timeline][timeline_item item_number=\"1\" title=\"Day 1: Leh\"]Pick up from the airport. Steep Mountains, pristine lakes, colourful Tibetan monasteries, a vibrant culture and the rugged terrain await you. You have rest of the day at leisure to acclimatise yourself to the high altitude of Ladakh. Overnight stay in a guesthouse.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"2\" title=\"Day 2: Leh: Thiksey, Shey, Leh Palace, Shanti Stupa\"]After breakfast we head to visit the oldest monastery in Ladakh- Thiksey Monastery and then Shey Palace. Mostly made of mud or wood, it has zero signs of grandeur or luxury just like any other palace in Ladakh. Before Leh, Shey used to be the capital of Ladakh. After Shey, lets head to Shanti stupa followed by old and beautiful Leh palace.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"3\" title=\"Day 3: Nubra Valley via Khardungla Pass (5602 Mt)\"]Nubra is a high altitude cold desert, the land of sand dunes and two humped  bactrian camels. This day we will cross the world’s highest motor able pass- Khardungla. Overnight stay at Samoor in Swiss tents.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"4\" title=\"Day 4: Samoor to Pangong Lake\"]Pangong Lake- where the famous 3 Idiots movie was filmed- is a high grassland lake at a height of 4350 Mt and extends from India to China. You can see China from the Indian side of this lake. This lake freezes completely during winters. Overnight stay in camps.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"5\" title=\"Day 5: Pangong to Leh via Changla Pass\"]This day we go back to Leh via Changla Pass. Changla Pass is the third highest motor able road in the world. A quiet and serene pathway takes you through sometimes steep and winding roads of the hills.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item][timeline_item item_number=\"6\" title=\"Day 6: Leh- local sight seeing\"]Visit Magnetic Hill, Hall of fame, Gurudwara Pathar Sahib and Confluence of Zanskar and Indus river. This is almost a spiritual sight where two completely different coloured entities merge together and yet remain separate and choose to flow harmoniously in a common direction. The difference in colours of the waters of the two merging rivers is interesting to see.[/timeline_item]\r\n\r\n[timeline_item item_number=\"7\" title=\"Day 7: Drop to the Airport\"]Time to bid adieu. With truckload of awesome memories to relish for the rest of our lives, today we say goodbye to Leh. Check out from the guest house and transfer to the airport for your onward journey.\r\n\r\n[/timeline_item]\r\n\r\n<strong>End of this memorable tour.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/timeline]\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Terms and Conditions\";s:7:\"content\";s:1118:\"<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Terms and conditions:</strong> Total trip cost: 25,500 INR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease note: we will not be liable for any claims or expenses arising from circumstances beyond our control such as accidents, injuries, delayed or cancelled flights/trains &amp; acts or forces of nature. Client will have to bear the charges of cancellation (if charged by the hotel &amp; other suppliers) arising due to delayed or cancelled flights/trains &amp; acts or forces of nature.\r\n\r\n<strong>Cancellation policy:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>75% of your booking amount will be refunded, if you cancel your participation before 45 days of the tour date.</li>\r\n 	<li>50% of yo