/span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Here is some information on what you can expect from your trip to Singapore:</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Language – Malay, Mandarin, Tamil, English</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Currency – Singapore Dollars</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Ways to reach your destination – Singapore is well connected by land, air and water too.</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Food – Chinese, Indian, Indonesian. It is very diverse!!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><u>Some other facts:</u></span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Singapore is commonly known as the lion city</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">It houses the famous Merlion</span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Chewing gums are not allowed in this country</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Places to visit and things to do in Singapore</span></strong></span>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>Sentosa Island</strong> – Our top pick in Singapore is Sentosa. This small island is a popular getaway for tourists and one of the most happening places in South East Asia. Famous for its 3 beaches- Siloso, Palawan, and Tanjong beach- this is a perfect destination for de-stressing, and exciting parties.</span><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1627\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/Tanjong_Beach_in_Sentosa.jpg\" alt=\"group-tours-singapore\" width=\"517\" height=\"388\" /></span><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>2.  A Visual Treat, the Merlion: </strong>The Merlion is Singapore’s mascot and has the head of a lion and the body of a fish. There are 7 Merlion statues in Singapore, however only 5 are recognized by the Singapore Tourism Board. </span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt\"><a href=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1638 size-large\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-1024x354.jpg\" alt=\"best things to do in singapore, singapore group tours\" width=\"748\" height=\"259\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>3. Clarke Quay and </strong><strong>Riverside</strong> : This festival village dedicated to good times, combining dining, shopping and a heritage inspired Disney-style adventure ride. Over Clarke Quay is Attica, famous for its outrageous parties.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1639\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-fun.jpg\" alt=\"just bucket list things, hidden secrets of singapore\" width=\"631\" height=\"265\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><strong> 4. The Universal Studios</strong>: Visit the most wowed upon place ever! The Sights, Games, Shows and Rides in this place leave you awestruck and make this the best part of your trip to Singapore.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1640\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-group-travel-1024x733.jpg\" alt=\"best places to visit while in singapore, bucket list things, just travel things\" width=\"535\" height=\"383\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 10pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Is Singapore in your bucket list? Check out this exciting 4Nights/5 Days group trip to Singapore from 25th January 2017 to 29th January 2017. Only for the young and lively. </span></strong><a href=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/tours/singapore-on-a-shoestring-group-trip/\">Singapore on a Shoestring Group Trip</a></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>5.</strong> <strong>Singapore Zoo and Night Safari</strong>: The Singapore Zoo is a must-see. It’s an open-air zoo, which is great because animals aren’t locked up in tiny cages</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1641 size-full\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-group-zoo.jpg\" alt=\"singapore group tour packages, your holiday agent\" width=\"498\" height=\"354\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><strong>6. Experience the beauty and delicacies of China Town: </strong>Hong Kong Temple in china town is made from the finest materials and best craftsmen that China had to offer around the time of its construction in the 1840s. The refreshed Chinatown Food Street celebrates the assembly of specialty dishes from main Chinese dialects and the different races in Singapore</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1643\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/Singapore-temple-travel-e1480950249217.jpg\" alt=\"places to visit in singapore, things to do in singapore, experience travelling\" width=\"429\" height=\"412\" /></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>7.</strong> <strong>Eat in Little India</strong>: Here you get interesting snacks, great vegetables, and oh-so-awesome food! This place has a large number of eating joints which offer authentic delicacies from India at very economical prices.</span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1644\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-tour-food.jpg\" alt=\"delicacies of singapore, best places to visit for food in singapore, tour packages\" width=\"566\" height=\"318\" /></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif;font-size: 14pt\"><strong>8. The Singapore River Cruise:</strong>  is one of the things most tourists enjoy. Taking a leisurely ride on the river cruise will take you past the landmarks of the Fullerton Hotel, Esplanade Singapore, The Merlion Park, Singapore Flyer and the latest attraction Marina Bay Sands Integrated Resort.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1646\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-cruise-travel-tour-group.jpg\" alt=\"hidden secrets of singapore, fun things to do in singapore, just travelling things\" width=\"604\" height=\"401\" /></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;font-family: \'times new roman\', times, serif\">Is Singapore in your bucket list? Check out this exciting 4Nights/5 Days group trip to Singapore from 25th January 2017 to 29th January 2017. Only for the young and lively.</s