span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Places to visit and things to do in Singapore:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Sentosa Island – Our top pick in Singapore is Sentosa.</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">It is the most popular getaway for tourists and one of the most happening places in South East Asia. It is famous for its beaches and the parties this island hosts. The Siloso, Palawan, and Tanjong Beaches are perfect for de-stressing, or for exciting parties.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1627 \" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/Tanjong_Beach_in_Sentosa.jpg\" alt=\"group-tours\" width=\"517\" height=\"388\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">A Visual Treat, the Merlion</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">The Merlion is Singapore’s mascot and has the head of a lion and the body of a fish. There are 7 Merlion statues in Singapore, however only 5 are recognized by the Singapore Tourism Board.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-1638 size-large aligncenter\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-1024x354.jpg\" alt=\"singapore-travel\" width=\"748\" height=\"259\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Clarke Quay</span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;font-family: \'comic sans ms\', sans-serif\">Riverside festival village dedicated to good times, combining dining, shopping and a heritage inspired Disney-style adventure ride. Over Clarke Quay is Attica, famous for its outrageous parties.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1639 \" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/singapore-travel-fun.j