<p style=\"text-align: left\"><span style=\"font-size: 24pt\"><strong>\r\n\r\nThe local attire :</strong></span></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em> </em></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>On daily basis, men in Cambodia wear t-shirts or shirts and full length trousers.</em></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Whereas women wear blouses and knee length skirts or sampots.\r\n</em></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Tourists visit Cambodia from all over the globe and no matter what dress code works for their country, it is appreciated when they follow the rules of the Cambodian attire.\r\n\r\n\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 24pt\"><strong>Cambodia and Women :\r\n</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Cambodia is a conserved country in terms of women wearing short skirts or shorts.</em></span></span></span>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1677\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"436\"]<img class=\" wp-image-1677\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/6.jpg\" alt=\"shorts,attention,not allowed,Cambodia manners\" width=\"436\" height=\"242\" /> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><strong>Something not appreciated in Cambodia</strong></span>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Women are also not allowed to be seen drinking in public.</em></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>In Cambodia, if a woman is seen with a man, he is expected to either be her husband or her fiancé.\r\nThese rules do not just imply to the local people, they are also meant for the tourists however, these rules are not so strictly enforced on them.</em></span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 24pt\">A humble advise to all:</span>\r\n\r\n\r\n</strong><em>Cambodian people are also kind of shy and take public display of affection to be quite offensive.\r\nThat is why tourists are advised not to display too much affection in public as less as holding one’s hand if the person is of another gender. So roaming around holding your partner’s hand in a big no no in Cambodia!\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1676\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"634\"]<img class=\" wp-image-1676\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/5.jpg\" alt=\"holding hands,physical display of affection,not liked\" width=\"634\" height=\"499\" /> <strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Don\'t click such pictures in Cambodia</span></strong>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><strong> </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>\r\n</em><span style=\"font-size: 24pt\"><strong>Greeting ethics of Cambodia:\r\n\r\n</strong></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>Cambodians are also very simple people, absolutely in contrast to their complex food. Usually they warmly greet the people by shaking their hands. However,women greet others by ‘sompeyar’ which is more or less Indian ‘Namastey’. The women join their palms with fingers pointing up and palms at chest level with their heads bent a little in order to welcome somebody.\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1679\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"748\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1679\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/sompeyar-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"sompeyar,hello,welcome,greeting,namastey\" width=\"748\" height=\"561\" /> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><strong>SOMPEYAR</strong></span>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>\r\n\r\nSompeyar is also done to pay respect to the monks and the lords.</em></span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1680\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"625\"]<img class=\" wp-image-1680\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/4-1.jpg\" alt=\"monks,Cambodia,sompeyar,greeting,respect\" width=\"625\" height=\"276\" /> <strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">A woman greeting the monks by Sompeyar</span></strong>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"><em>For people who are used to wearing short dresses and shorts, it is a very different kind of experience, something that is elegant in its own way.\r\nNow knowing how easy and simple it is to be in Cambodia, one would definitely pay a visit to this extremely beautiful place.</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt\"> #Cambodia #sompeyar #sampot #Vietnam #Thailand #etiquettes #dresses #Cambodianpeople #Asiancountries</span>','Dressing and Etiquettes File - CAMBODIA STYLE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1671-revision-v1','','','2016-12-09 20:28:49','2016-12-09 20:28:49','',1671,'http://yourholidayagent.com/1671-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1685,10,'2016-12-11 10:20:42','2016-12-11 10:20:42','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Have you ever thought of a destination from where you are standing at one end of a continent and see another? </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\" style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><strong>Gibraltar</strong> is one such unique place on earth ! Gibraltar is a British Overseas Territory and headland, on Spain\'s south coast in Europe. The <strong>Strait of Gibraltar</strong> is a narrow strait that connects the Atlantic Ocean to the Mediterranean Sea and separates Gibraltar and Peninsular Spain in Europe from Morocco and Ceuta (Spain) in Africa.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span style=\"font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Ceuta</b> is a Spanish autonomous city located on the north coast of Africa. </span><span class=\"s1\">You can look out across <b>Ceuta\'s port</b> and, on clear days enjoy you