fting\" width=\"700\" height=\"467\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nExplore the hidden secrets of Sikkim in a small group. Check out this unique trip to Sikkim:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/tours/sikkim-darjeeling-group-trip/\">Sikkim-Darjeeling Group Trip</a>','River Rafting In Kolad','','publish','open','closed','','river-rafting-in-kolad','','','2017-01-24 07:46:30','2017-01-24 07:46:30','',0,'http://yourholidayagent.com/?p=1797',0,'post','',0),(1802,16,'2017-01-18 13:09:22','2017-01-18 13:09:22','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1798\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/kolad-river-rafting-5-mumbai-travellers.jpg\" alt=\"Things-to-do-in-kolad, river-rafting-in kolad, river-rafting-in-india\" width=\"550\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1801\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/Koladrafting.jpg\" alt=\"Water-activities-in-kolad, water-activities-in-india\" width=\"591\" height=\"394\" />\r\n\r\nFor people looking for a place for a small trip, kolad can definitely be a great option!!\r\nIt is a few kilometers away from Mumbai and lies on the Mumbai - Pune Highway.\r\nThe place is simply magnificent! The journey itself to kolad is very pretty where one crosses the beautiful locations like Lonavala and Khandala.\r\nAdventurous activities like river rafting is very famous of Kolad. The rafting session stretches for about 12km in the Kundalika river.. The entire experience of river rafting gets more fun when the water fight amongst all boats begins.\r\nIt is an amazing place for a weekend!\r\nThe hotels, food, place, people everything is so nice that one would surely want to plan another visit to Kolad!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1800\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/rafting-at-kolad-img_1060.jpg\" alt=\"Water-sports-in-kolad, things-to-do-in-kolad\" width=\"700\" height=\"467\" />','River Rafting In Kolad','','inherit','closed','closed','','1797-revision-v1','','','2017-01-18 13:09:22','2017-01-18 13:09:22','',1797,'http://yourholidayagent.com/1797-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1803,1,'2017-01-19 07:17:34','2017-01-19 07:17:34','<h1 style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif; font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>D</strong><strong>ressing</strong><strong> and Etiquettes -</strong></span></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif; font-size: 36pt;\"><strong>CAMBODIA STYLE </strong><strong>!</strong></span></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Every country has its own culture, be it for food, clothing, songs, language, anything. Well Cambodia too has its unique culture which has been influenced by many neighbouring countries yet still has its own identity.\r\nDue to the severe impact of its history on the culture, the traditional attires of Cambodia are very intriguing yet very simple.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1678\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"748\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1678\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/Cambodiacostumesmall-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"Cambodian dress,sampot,sampot,blouse,head gear\" width=\"748\" height=\"499\" /> <strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Cambodia\'s Traditional Attire</span></strong>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;\"><em>\r\n</em> </span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Cambodia cannot be termed as ‘backward<span style=\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;\">’ but yes, it is still very reserved compared to many other countries in the world.</span></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">The local attire :</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><em> </em></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">On daily basis, men in Cambodia wear t-shirts or shirts and full length trousers.</span></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Whereas women wear blouses and knee length skirts or sampots.\r\n</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Tourists visit Cambodia from all over the globe and no matter what dress code works for their country, it is appreciated when they follow the rules of the Cambodian attire.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 24pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">Cambodia and Women :</span>\r\n</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Cambodia is a conserved country in terms of women wearing short skirts or shorts. </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1787\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/dress.jpg\" alt=\"things-to-do-in-cambodia,what-to-wear-in-cambodia\" width=\"720\" height=\"960\" /></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Women are also not allowed to be seen drinking in public.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: disc;\">\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">In Cambodia, if a woman is seen with a man, he is expected to either be her husband or her fiancé.\r\nThese rules do not just imply to the local people, they are also meant for the tourists however, these rules are not so strictly enforced on them.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><strong>A humble advise to all:</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Cambodian people are also kind of shy and take public display of affection to be quite offensive.</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> That is why tourists are advised not to display too much affection in public as less as holding one’s hand if the person is of another gender. So roaming around holding your partner’s hand in a big no no in Cambodia!</span><em>\r\n</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong> </strong><em>\r\n</em><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><strong>Greeting ethics of Cambodia:</strong></span></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Cambodians are also very simple people, absolutely in contrast to their complex food. Usually they warmly greet the people by shaking their hands. However,women greet others by ‘sompeyar’ which is more or less Indian ‘Namastey’. The women join their palms with fingers pointing up and palms at chest level with their heads bent a little in order to welcome somebody.</span><em>\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1679\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"748\"]<img class=\"size-large wp-image-1679\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/sompeyar-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"sompeyar,hello,welcome,greeting,namastey\" width=\"748\" height=\"561\" /> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>ACTION OF SOMPEYAR</strong></span>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSompeyar is also done to pay respect to the monks and the lords.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_1680\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"625\"]<img class=\" wp-image-1680\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/4-1.jpg\" alt=\"monks,Cambodia,sompeyar,greeting,respect\" width=\"625\" height=\"276\" /> <strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">A woman greeting the monks by Sompeyar</span></strong>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">For people who are used to wearing short dresses and shorts, it is a very different kind of experience, something that is elegant in its own way.\r\nNow knowing how easy and simple it is to be in Cambodia, one would definitely pay a visit to this extremely beautiful place, won\'t you?\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> #Cambodia #sompeyar #sampot #Vietnam #Thailand #etiquettes #dresses #Cambodianpeople #Asiancountries</span>','Dressing and Etiquettes - CAMBODIA STYLE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1671-revision-v1','','','2017-01-19 07:17:34','2017-01-19 07:17:34','',1671,'http://yourholidayagent.com/1671-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1804,1,'2017-01-19 12:52:44','2017-01-19 12:52:44','','Order &ndash; January 19, 2017 @ 12:52 PM','','wc-cancelled','open','closed','order_5880a5f31bf7b','order-jan-19-2017-1141-am','','','2017-01-19 12:52:44','2017-01-19 12:52:44','',0,'http://yourholidayagent.com/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=1804',0,'shop_order','',1),(1805,16,'2017-01-20 17:51:01','2017-01-20 17:51:01','','kolad-river-rafting','','inherit','open','closed','','kolad-river-rafting','','','2017-01-20 17:55:41','2017-01-20 17:55:41','',0,'http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/kolad-river-rafting.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1806,16,'2017-01-20 17:51:05','2017-01-20 17:51:05','','place-for-rafting-kolad','','inherit','open','closed','','place-for-rafting-kolad','','','2017-01-20 17:52:41','2017-01-20 17:52:41','',1797,'http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/place-for-rafting-kolad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1807,16,'2017-01-20 17:51:10','2017-01-20 17:51:10','','rafting-at-kolad','','inherit','open','closed','','rafting-at-kolad','','','2017-01-20 17:54:40','2017-01-20 17:54:40','',1797,'http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/rafting-at-kolad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1808,16,'2017-01-20 17:51:14','2017-01-20 17:51:14','','things-to-do-in-kolad','','inherit','open','closed','','things-to-do-in-kolad','','','2017-01-20 17:53:36','2017-01-20 17:53:36','',1797,'http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/things-to-do-in-kolad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1809,16,'2017-01-20 17:56:22','2017-01-20 17:56:22','<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1806\" src=\"http://yourholidayagent.com/wp-content/uploads/place-for-rafting-kolad.jpg\" alt=\"things-to-do-in-kolad, river-rafting-in-india\" width=\